olive oil
½ tin sweetcorn
1 stalk celery
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 sachet Mild Caribbean Jerk Seasoning
1 tsp honey
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Mayonnaise
1 tsp white wine vinegar
1 packet Parsley

• Drain sweetcorn (see ingredients).
• Thinly slice celery.
• Cut pork loin steaks into 1cm strips.
• In a medium bowl, combine pork strips, mild Caribbean jerk seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil.

Little cooks: Take charge by combining the ingredients!

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook sweetcorn until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are ‘popping’ out.

• Return frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook pork strips in batches, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Add the honey and toss to coat.
• Meanwhile, microwave mini flourtortillas on a plate for 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

TIP: Cooking the pork in batches over high heat helps it stay tender.

• Add shredded cabbage mix, celery, mayonnaise and a drizzle of white wine vinegar to the bowl with the charred corn. Season to taste and toss to combine.
• Top tortillas with celery slaw and Caribbean pork. Tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Take the lead and help build the tacos!